  "notes": "The EA888 Gen 3 1.8T (internal designation CJSA/CJSB/CPKA/CPRA depending on market and tune) represents a significant improvement over the Gen 1 and Gen 2 EA888. Key Gen 3 features include dual VVT (variable valve timing on both intake and exhaust camshafts), a Roots-type low-pressure exhaust gas recirculation system, an integrated exhaust manifold cast directly into the cylinder head (reduces warm-up time and improves turbo response), and a closed-deck aluminum block. The turbocharger is a twin-scroll unit on most variants. Compression ratio is 9.6:1. This engine is the stock unit in the VW Golf Alltrack (Mk7 platform), and is direct-injection only in most applications. It shares its architecture with the Gen 3b 2.0T, differing primarily in stroke. Compatible transaxles include the 6-speed MQ250 (manual) and DQ250 (DSG). Well-supported aftermarket; common Stage 1 tune yields approximately 215-225hp with no hardware changes.",
